SIMPLE: medalist
RECORDS: 1

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Medalist
<hw>Med"al*ist</hw>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[Cf. F.
<ets>m⟦eacute⟧dailliste</ets>, It. <ets>medaglista</ets>.]</ety>
<altsp>[Written also <asp>medallist</asp>.]</altsp>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>1.</sn> <def>A person that is skilled or curious in medals; a
collector of medals.</def> <rj><au>Addison.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>A designer of medals.</def>
<rj><au>Macaulay.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>3.</sn> <def>One who has gained a medal as the reward of merit;
<as>as, the gold <ex>medalist</ex> in downhill skiing</as>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Medallic</ent>⟦br⟧
